<div class="c2"><h1>Antonio Valente</h1></div>
<div class="c2"><h3>(fl. 1565-80)</h3></div>

<br />


<p class="c1">Italian (or possibly Spanish) organist and composer. He was blind, and from 1565 to 1580 was organist at S. Angelo a Nilo (or Nido) in Naples. His<i> Intavolatura</i> of 1576, written in an unusual number notation, contains the earliest known written-out fantasia for keyboard, imitative ricercars, and variations which use stereotyped figurations. He also published a volume of canons for organ, <i>Versi spirituali</i> (Naples, 1580).</p><br /><br />

<br />



